Usage: run_simulations.py [options]

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -B BENCHMARK_LIST, --benchmark_list=BENCHMARK_LIST
                        a comma seperated list of benchmark suites to run. See
                        apps/define-*.yml for the benchmark suite names.
  -C CONFIGS_LIST, --configs_list=CONFIGS_LIST
                        a comma seperated list of configs to run. See
                        configs/define-*.yml for the config names.
  -p BENCHMARK_EXEC_PREFIX, --benchmark_exec_prefix=BENCHMARK_EXEC_PREFIX
                        When submitting the job to torque this string is
                        placed before the command line that runs the
                        benchmark.  Useful when wanting to run valgrind.
  -r RUN_DIRECTORY, --run_directory=RUN_DIRECTORY
                        Name of directory in which to run simulations
  -n, --no_launch       When set, no torque jobs are launched.  However, all
                        the setup for running is performed. ie, the run
                        directories are created and are ready to run. This can
                        be useful when you want to create a new configuration,
                        but want to test it locally before  launching a bunch
                        of jobs.
  -s SIMULATOR_DIR, --simulator_dir=SIMULATOR_DIR
                        Point this to the directory that your .so is stored
                        in. If nothing is input here - the scripts will assume
                        that you are using the so built in GPGPUSIM_ROOT or
                        ACCELSIM_ROOT.
  -N LAUNCH_NAME, --launch_name=LAUNCH_NAME
                        Pass if you want to name the launch. This will
                        determine the name of the logfile. If you do not name
                        the file, it will just use the current date/time.
  -T TRACE_DIR, --trace_dir=TRACE_DIR
                        Pass this option to run the simulator in trace-driven
                        mode. The directory passed should be the root of all
                        the trace files.
  -M JOB_MEM, --job_mem=JOB_MEM
                        Memory usgae of the job be sure to specify the units
                        i.e. 4G, 900M, etc..
  -l LAUNCHER, --launcher=LAUNCHER
                        Specify how jobs will be launched. Select one of
                        sbatch (slurm), qsub (torque), local. By default, we
                        test for slurm, then torque, then just use local if
                        you have neither.
  -c CORES, --cores=CORES
                        Specify the core limit when using procman. If nothing
                        is specified, all the cores on the local node will be
                        used.
  -a, --accelwattch_HW  Enable passing hw_perf_bench_name for accelwattch hw
                        and hybrid runs to config file.
